        <h2 class="section-col-title">
          Conservation isn't just for experts, <span class="highlight-container">it's for you</span>.</h2>
        <div class="col-content">
          <p>We get it &mdash; the environment is a big, scary topic. There's industry jargon, political stances, and proposed solutions that are too complex for the everyday person to fully understand.</p>
          <p>But the fact of the matter is, the environment is everything, including each of us. You don't have to understand how the <a class="text-link" href="https://outdoornebraska.gov/learn/nebraska-wildlife/nebraska-plants/colorado-butterfly-plant/" target="_blank">Colorado butterfly plant</a> requires ultra-specific conditions to thrive; or even the inner-workings of why climate change is one of the <a class="text-link" href="https://www.un.org/en/global-issues/climate-change" target="_blank">biggest problems</a> humanity faces  - you only need a little curiosity, empathy, and recognition of interconnectedness. That's where we come in.</p>
        </div>
